21/05/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Prime Minister Plamen Panayotov said on Thursday (20 May) the country might broaden its participation in the international mission in Afghanistan. 
He added that the increase would probably be made in co-operation with Germany and that Bulgaria could contribute logistical support. 
Later in the day, the Chief of General Staff of the Army General Nikola Kolev said a feasibility study is being conducted. 
(BTA, BNT, BNR - 20/05/04)
